titlestmt.titleproper: Guide to the Yale Events and Activities Photographs
titlestmt.author: compiled by Daniel Hartwig

publicationstmt.publisher: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace on Friday January 11, 2019 at 09:04

repository.corpname: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

did.abstract: The materials consist of press photos taken by the Office of Public Affairs, formerly known as the News Bureau and the Office of Public Information to document events and activities at Yale.

origination.label: creator
origination.corpname: Yale University. Office of Public Affairs

odd.head: General note
odd.p: Forms part of Yale Record Group 48-A (YRG 48-A), Yale pictorial records and collections.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Yale Events and Activities Photographs (RU 690). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The photographs are arranged in four series: I. Photographs, 1852-1974. II. Photographs, 1950-circa 1994. III. Slides and transparencies, circa 1974-1989. IV. Oversize images, 1916, and subsequent accessions.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The materials consist of press photos taken by the Office of Public Affairs, formerly known as the News Bureau and the Office of Public Information to document events and activities at Yale.
